0 -12 Td (6.1 How Section 5 modules compose) Tj
0 -12 Td (* Section 5 artifacts are intermediate outputs.) Tj
0 -12 Td (* Section 6 algorithm consumes those artifacts to produce final chain verdicts.) Tj
0 -12 Td () Tj
0 -12 Td (Mapping:) Tj
0 -12 Td (* `sink_roots.json` -> root selection.) Tj
0 -12 Td (* `channel_graph.json` -> tunnel jump.) Tj
0 -12 Td (* `derive/check` -> semantic decision inputs.) Tj
0 -12 Td (* `chains.json` -> final linker output from M9.1.) Tj
0 -12 Td () Tj
0 -12 Td (6.2 Pseudocode) Tj
0 -12 Td () Tj
0 -12 Td (for sink in sink_roots:) Tj
0 -12 Td (    for root in sink.roots:) Tj
0 -12 Td (        path = backward_slice\(root, budget=B\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (        while path.hit_object_node\(\):) Tj
0 -12 Td (            producers = topk_producers\(path.object_id, K\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (            path = tunnel_jump_and_continue\(path, producers, budget=B\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (        derive = summarize_derive\(path\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (        checks = summarize_checks\(path, sink.site\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (        verdict = score_and_decide\(path, derive, checks\)) Tj
0 -12 Td (        emit_chain\(sink, root, path, derive, checks, verdict\)) Tj
0 -12 Td () Tj
0 -12 Td () Tj
0 -12 Td (6.3 Complexity and why heuristics are necessary) Tj
0 -12 Td (Without sink-first \(`source x sink`\):) Tj
0 -12 Td (* Approx complexity: `O\(|Src| * |Sink| * C_slice\)`.) Tj
